{
  "texts": [
    "MARL allows agents to perform actions at different time steps and independent training parameters and policy structures.",
    "The shared goal of both agents is to minimize the makespan.",
    "The developed control algorithm is thus a cooperative, asynchronous, heterogeneous MARL algorithm (cf.",
    "The underlying problem is formulated as a Decentralized Partially Observable Markov Decision Process with separate rewards.",
    "The Decentralized Partially Observable Markov Decision Process generalizes the Partially Observable Markov Decision Process to multiple agents and thus can be used to model a team of cooperative agents situated in a stochastic, partially observable environment."
  ]
}